    "history":  {
                    "short_description":  "A popular city beach known for its wide sandy shore and proximity to Trivandrum Airport.",
                    "detailed":  "Shanghumugham Beach has long been a favorite evening spot for the residents of Thiruvananthapuram. Its popularity grew with its proximity to the airport and the installation of the iconic \u0027Matsya Kanyaka\u0027 (Mermaid) sculpture by the renowned artist Kanayi Kunhiraman in 1990. The beach is a venue for various cultural events and religious rituals, including the \u0027Bali Tharpanam\u0027 ceremony. It offers a spacious promenade, a children\u0027s park, and food stalls, making it a complete family destination."
                },
